Anniston is a city in , and county seat of , Calhoun County in the state of Alabama , United States .
As of the 2000 census , the population of the city is 24,276 .
According to the 2005 U.S. Census estimates , the city had a population of 23,741 .
In 2002 , an investigation by 60 minutes showed Anniston was among the most toxic cities in the country .
The main source of local contamination was a Monsanto chemical factory , which was closed .
